  "prompt": "How do you play disc golf competitively?",
  "response": "To play disc golf competitively:\n\n1. Learn the rules\n- Follow PDGA (Professional Disc Golf Association) official rules\n- Understand scoring and throwing techniques\n- Know course etiquette\n\n2. Equipment needed\n- Multiple discs (drivers, mid-range, putters)\n- Disc golf bag\n- Comfortable athletic clothing and shoes\n\n3. Training and skill development\n- Practice throwing techniques\n- Work on accuracy and distance\n- Learn different throwing styles (backhand, forehand)\n\n4. Tournaments\n- Register with PDGA for official events\n- Start with local amateur tournaments\n- Progress to regional and national competitions\n\n5. Scoring\n- Count total throws per hole\n- Lowest total score wins\n- Penalties for out-of-bounds or missed shots\n\n6. Divisions\n- Compete in age and skill-based divisions\n- Divisions include Professional, Advanced, Intermediate, Recreational\n\n7. Physical and mental preparation\n- Develop physical fitness\n- Practice mental focus and strategy\n- Learn course management\n\n8. Networking\n- Join local disc golf clubs\n- Attend league nights\n- Connect with other players\n\nConsistent practice, learning, and participation in events are key to competitive disc golf success.",
